From: Joey Riches <josephriches@gmail.com>
Date: Sat, 27 Jun 2026 15:15:48 +0100
Subject: [PATCH 1/2] backends/eopkg: Adjust percentage callbacks for eopkg
 v5.0.0

eopkg 5 adds support for concurrent downloads, additionally, implicit
package downloads are no longer supported through initializing
`pisi.package.Package()` objects. Instead, `PackageResource` objects
are initialized and explicitly fetched instead.

For the packagekit backend, not too many changes are required, we:
- Listen to fetching_overall callbacks to get global download progress
  instead of tracking current/overall packages completed.
- Grab PackageResource objects from the downloading notify event instead
  of full fat packages objects.
- Cleanup some unnecessary tracking
---
 backends/eopkg/eopkgBackend.py | 41 ++++++++++++++++++++++------------
 1 file changed, 27 insertions(+), 14 deletions(-)

diff --git a/backends/eopkg/eopkgBackend.py b/backends/eopkg/eopkgBackend.py
